data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer takes an expression tree

The parameter changed from `Expression<Func<…>>` to `Func<…>`, so your manual expression-tree construction **won't compile**. The fix is dramatically simpler:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Parameter` plumbing — it's no longer needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & use full path

**Two changes combine here:**

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column silently. Now EF appends a number to disambiguate (e.g. `Street` and `Street1`), which **will break existing databases**.
- **Nested full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`. Now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** — pin column names explicitly to preserve your schema:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin to the old (short) name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now requires a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** method signatures on the interface accordingly.
